  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Workplace Safety and Health Officer",
  "description": "<p>Job Description: </p><ul><li>Responsible for the implementation and monitoring of Workplace Safety & Health and Environment Management Systems at work sites.</li><li>Conduct regular WSH inspections and follow-up actions to ensure safety compliance</li><li>Ensure all Health & Safety policies, procedures, rules and regulations are adhered to and are regularly reviewed, updated and communicated.</li><li>Ensure the Company meets its statutory obligations in all areas pertaining to health, safety and welfare at work, including statutory training and reporting.</li><li>Ensure the completion and regular review of risk assessments for all work equipments and operations.</li><li>Ensure all accidents are documented, investigated and recommended improvements implemented.</li><li>Coordinate the development of health & safety policies, systems of work and procedures.</li><li>Inspect project sites to ensure safety measure are being carried out at all times.</li></ul><p>Requirements：</p><ul><li><strong>At least 3 years of experience as a Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) Officer, preferably with LTA or building & construction projects.</strong></li><li><strong>Certifications in Workplace Safety and Health Officer (WSHO) with MOM.</strong></li><li>Possess good communication skills.</li><li>Strong leadership and communication skills.</li><li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team.</li><li>Attention to detail and strong organizational skills.</li><li>Must be responsible, organized, and self-initiated.</li><li>Respect for deadlines, sense of urgency.</li></ul>",
